  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Maria Weston Chapman requests a contribution to the Liberty Bell either in prose or poetry, &quot;in German, Danish or English.&quot; She explains the purpose of the Liberty Bell. In the letter, Chapman refers to a &quot;severe domestic calamity&quot; which prevented her from making this request seasonably. [The &quot;domestic calamity&quot; referred to, was presumably the death of Maria Weston Chapman&apos;s father-in-law, Henry Chapman.]</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Includes, accompanying envelope with the delivery address: To Harro-Harreng, Esq., Care of S. H. Gay, Esq., New York, 142 Nassau Street.</subfield>
  </datafield>
